Floating Price:

The mean of the arithmetic average of the daily high and low quotations for=
=20
Dated Brent under the heading 'Platt's Crude Oil Marketwire: Brent (DTD)' a=
s=20
reported in Platt's Crude Oil Marketwire minus the average of the daily=20
settlement prices for the prompt month of the IPE Brent Crude Oil Futures=
=20
Contract for each Commodity Business Day/Trading Day for the applicable=20
Determination Period, with the exception of the last Commodity Business=20
Day/Trading Day of the prompt month on which day the settlement price for t=
he=20
Second Nearby Month will be used.  The calculation should include only the=
=20
days when both the IPE is open and Platts publish their dated Brent=20
assessment.

Common Pricing:

Pricing to be effective only on the days when both the IPE is open and Plat=
ts=20
publish their dated Brent assessment.



